#. Tag: para
#: configuring.docbook:1131
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Additionally, document variables can be placed in a file called "
#| "<filename>.kateconfig</filename> in any directory, and the configured "
#| "settings will be applied as if the modelines were entered on every file "
#| "in the directory and its subdirectories, as far down as the <link linkend="
#| "\"pref-open-save-advanced\">configured search depth.</link> Document "
#| "variables in <filename>.kateconfig</filename> use the same syntax as in "
#| "modelines."
msgid ""
"Additionally, document variables can be placed in a file called <filename>."
"kateconfig</filename> in any directory, and the configured settings will be "
"applied as if the modelines were entered on every file in the directory and "
"its subdirectories. Document variables in <filename>.kateconfig</filename> "
"use the same syntax as in modelines, but with <link linkend=\"kateconfig-"
"extended-options\">extended options</link>."
msgstr ""
"De plus, les variables de document peuvent être placées dans un fichier "
"appelé <filename>.kateconfig</filename> dans n'importe quel dossier, et les "
"réglages configurés seront appliqués si les lignes de mode ont été saisies "
"dans chaque fichier dans le dossier et ses sous-dossiers, aussi profond que "
"la <link linkend=\"pref-open-save-advanced\">profondeur de recherche du "
"fichier de configuration</link>. Les variables de document dans <filename>."
"kateconfig</filename> utilisent la même syntaxe que les lignes de mode."

#. Tag: para
#: configuring.docbook:1137
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "There are variables to support almost all configurations in katepart, and "
#| "additionally plugins can use variables, in which case it should be "
#| "documented in the plugin's documentation."
msgid ""
"There are variables to support almost all configurations in &kappname;, and "
"additionally plugins can use variables, in which case it should be "
"documented in the plugin's documentation."
